# Walkin Portal - User Manual

## Introduction
The **Walkin Portal** is a high-performance recruitment management system designed for high-volume walk-in drives. It streamlines the entire process from candidate registration to the final offer, ensuring real-time tracking and data synchronization.

---

## 1. Getting Started: The Home Portal
The Home screen is your central hub for all operational activities. From here, you can access the four primary modules:

- **Add Candidate**: Synchronize walk-in data from external sources (Google Forms/Sheets).
- **Add Interviewer**: Onboard technical panel members and map their expertise.
- **Pre-Screen**: Manage early-stage processing (Orientation, GD, Aptitude).
- **Dashboard**: Monitor live metrics and the candidate pipeline in real-time.

---

## 2. Candidate & Interviewer Management

### Adding Candidates
- Use the **Add Candidate** module to link external data sources.
- Ensure Google Forms/Sheets are correctly connected to automate ingestion.
- **Tip**: Verify sync status after each batch to avoid data gaps.

### Managing Interviewers
- Use the **Add Interviewer** module to register new panel members.
- Expertise mapping allows for efficient scheduling during L1 and L2 rounds.

---

## 3. Pre-Screening Hub
The Pre-Screening Hub is designed for high-efficiency bulk processing of candidates through the initial stages.

### Workflow Stages
The hub follows a linear progression:
1. **Orientation**: Capture candidate agreement to terms and work conditions.
2. **Group Discussion (GD)**: Manage bulk assessment of communication skills.
3. **Aptitude**: Track assessment scores and set assignments.

### Batch Controls
- **ID Range Filtering**: Focus on specific groups of candidates by setting a "From ID" and "To ID" range.
- **Bulk Updates**: Select multiple candidates at once and update their status to "Selected", "Hold", or "Rejected".
- **Aptitude Management**: Assign specific "SETS" (1-5) to candidates and record their marks (0-25) directly.

---

## 4. Dashboard & Pipeline Tracking
The Dashboard provides a 360-degree view of your recruitment drive.

### Real-Time Metrics (KPIs)
- **Total Footfall**: Total candidates registered.
- **Selected**: Candidates who have cleared all rounds.
- **Rejected**: Total candidates who did not meet requirements.
- **Stage Metrics**: Real-time count of candidates currently in Orientation, GD, Aptitude, L1, L2, and HR.

### Candidate Search & Details
- **Search**: Quickly find candidates by Name or ID.
- **Filters**: Filter the view by Role/Position or Experience (Experienced vs. Fresher).
- **Candidate Drawer**: Click on any candidate to view their complete history, including timestamps and interviewer notes.
- **Update Status**: Use the "Update" button to manually adjust a candidate's progress if needed.

### Data Export
- Use the **Export to Excel** button to download the current state of the candidate pipeline for offline reporting.

---

## 5. Operational Guidelines & Best Practices

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Real-Time Sync**: The portal syncs data to the master sheet in real-time. Always check the "Last Sync" timestamp on the Dashboard.

> [!TIP]
> **Data Integrity**: Regularly remove duplicate registrations to keep metrics accurate.

- **Process Flow**: Ensure interviewers are assigned before candidates move to L1/L2 rounds.
- **Timestamps**: All actions are recorded in **IST** for consistency across the team.
- **Manual Overrides**: If a sync fails, use the manual "Refresh" button on the Dashboard to re-fetch the latest data.




